article.headline: Fla. International 69, Florida Atlantic 58
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Kenneth White scored a game-high 17 points as Florida International beat Florida Atlantic on Saturday night. Alex Galindo added 12 points for Florida International (4-9, 1-2 Sun Belt Conference) and Nikola Gacesa finished with eight rebounds and 13 points. Carderro Nwoji scored 13 points for Florida Atlantic (4-11, 0-4), Brett Royster had 10 and Paul Graham III added nine points. Royster, Nwoji and Derrick Simmons also each pulled down six rebounds for Florida Atlantic.
